INSERT INTO `projects` VALUES (17,'Marine Bank & Trust','Marine Bank & Trust needed to differentiate its brand in a crowded market and generate new customer acquisitions.','After recovering from the recession that hit South Florida and The Treasure Coast, Marine Bank found itself without an active internal or external marketing plan. They had previously positioned themselves as a locally owned community bank. But this approach alone was not gaining significant traction in a competitive market with a seasonal population. With only 3% share in a slow-growth market, Marine Bank knew it was time to re-evaluate their brand in order to grow their customer base.','<p>Current360 began with a comprehensive review of the bank’s current brand and all internal/external processes. We identified every customer touch point, then measured service effectiveness. We surveyed the market (and beyond) and performed an extensive competitive analysis. And we spoke with current and potential customers to find out their biggest banking needs.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our research revealed the need to refocus Marine Bank’s brand identity to a financial institution that was nimble and empowered to make decisions. All without losing the appeal of personal service that customers expect from a community bank.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We also discovered the bank was constrained by their current market area. Marine Bank is located in one of the wealthiest zip codes in Florida, but expansion offered significant growth opportunities among demographics outside their existing customer base. Plus, to level the playing field against larger banks, Marine Bank needed to offer additional services.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Current360 first created an expansion plan that included new geographic areas and additional lines of business to reach potential consumers. Next, a marketing campaign was developed around the positioning line, “Empowered to take you anywhere,” to communicate quick, local decisions.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We utilized testimonials to highlight customer experiences with small business loans and fast, responsive service. This approach also validated the Marine Bank’s claim that – as a locally owned community bank – they provided better service than large corporate banks. The campaign launched with highly targeted direct mail, but messaging was reinforced online, through social media efforts and in the bank’s newsletters.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Of course, we had to ensure that Marine Bank’s people were all on the same page. Current360 implemented a robust training component to educate employees on internal and external branding. Then we focused on new customer acquisitions by improving their selling, networking and business development skills.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Beyond the marketing campaign and expansion plans, Marine Bank established a strategic partnership with LPL Financial, a wealth management group. This relationship created a well-defined referral system to generate new customers for the bank.</p>','The campaign has been so successful, Marine Bank expanded into three surrounding counties. The bank has also added wealth management to its product line and now offers mobile banking and mobile check deposits to appeal to younger, more sophisticated markets. ','Placeholder Marine Bank Quote','A. Person',0,'main.jpg',NULL,NULL,'MarineBankLogo.jpg',NULL,'2015-05-21 16:08:09','2015-05-22 15:43:23','marine-bank-trust'),(18,'Frazier History Museum','The Frazier History Museum needed to create excitement and drive ticket sales for its summer exhibition, Gridiron Glory: The Best of the Pro Football Hall of Fame.\r\n','We knew that traditional male sports fans and nostalgia enthusiasts would be naturally drawn to this exhibit. But, for the campaign to be truly successful, we needed to expand our audience by speaking directly to moms and families.\r\n','<p>The Gridiron Glory exhibit contains much more than just 200 rare football artifacts across 5000 square feet. It also features interactive multimedia experiences and hands-on activities for visitors of all ages. To convey all that the exhibition offered – and to speak to a wide audience – we needed to create a dynamic television spot to spearhead our campaign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our concept recreated the raw emotion a person experiences the first time they see a favorite player’s game-worn uniform, a relic from an unforgettable game played generations ago or the Vince Lombardi Super Bowl Trophy. To maximize the impact, we showed these reactions in ultra slo-mo with a soundtrack reminiscent of NFL Films and a John Facenda inspired voiceover.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We then complemented the television spot with a series of outdoor and digital executions. Each of these played on the accomplishments of individual Pro Football Hall of Fame members who were featured at the exhibit. We also partnered with several sports radio stations to stay top-of-mind with our core audience, and even organized the first live remote from the museum.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Beyond generating ticket sales for the Gridiron Glory exhibit, we also wanted visitors to enjoy their overall experience at the Frazier History Museum. This would help to encourage ticket sales for future exhibitions and help establish an affinity for the museum throughout the community. While our primary goal was to draw in football fans, we ultimately wanted every visitor to leave as a Frazier fan.</p>\r\n','<p>As soon as the Kentucky Derby concluded, the Frazier History Museum’s campaign kicked into full gear. Over the course of the summer, attendance for Gridiron Glory grew steadily each month with visitors from Louisville and beyond attending the exhibit.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Current360 also received accolades within our own industry. The outdoor executions were finalists for a Digital Out-Of-Home Viewers Choice Award. And our social media campaign received special recognition from Twitter.</p>','Our work with the Frazier History Museum was exciting to our team for a number of reasons. With an agency full of sports nuts, the opportunity to create a campaign around Hall of Fame football players was thrilling. But equally as important was the chance to reach new audiences who had never visited the Frazier.','Harry Mulkey',11,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-21 17:20:05','2015-05-22 15:43:23','frazier-history-museum'),(19,'WaterStep','An international organization that saves lives through safe water needed a brand identity that would reflect their mission and their methods of support.','<p>The organization, originally named EDGE Outreach, works to save lives at risk from waterborne illness in developing communities and disaster areas, including Haiti, Kenya, India, the Dominican Republic, China, Uganda and Costa Rica.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Their approach combines practical training with readily available technology to empower self-sufficiency at the local level. The organization finances their mission primarily through a shoe-recycling program that generates operating funds, while also promoting micro-business opportunities and reducing landfill volume.</p>','<p>The organization provides safe drinking water for hundreds of thousands of people around the world. But nothing about the name EDGE Outreach made that clear to potential donors or charitable organizations.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>After several strategic planning sessions with EDGE’s Board of Directors, Current360 set off to find a new name that reflected their primary goal of addressing the root causes of waterborne illness.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The name WaterStep does much more than that.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>While it speaks directly to the organization’s key benefit, it also establishes a direct connection to their primary source of financial support. WaterStep is intuitive, whether someone sees it on a business card, on a repaired well pump or on the side of a shoe donation box.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Once the name was approved, Current360 developed a new logo, website and complete identity package to round out the new brand.</p>','This new name and logo have helped position the organization among other national and international groups who are fighting for support dollars. The shoe program has grown by more than 25% and expanded into 8 states. More important, safe drinking water has been brought to more than a quarter million people around the world.','Placeholder WaterStep Quote','A. Person',7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-21 17:22:05','2015-05-22 15:43:23','waterstep'),(20,'OraStrip','OraStrip® QuickCheck Canine needed to raise awareness among dog owners of potential dental issues that their dogs may face.','OraStrip QuickCheck Canine is the first diagnostic test used to detect active periodontal disease that veterinarians can’t see during a visual exam. With up to 60% of a dog’s tooth lying beneath the gumline, a visual exam is simply not enough. Earlier detection of periodontal disease helps prevent painful tooth and bone loss, and – if left untreated – the infection can lead to kidney, liver and heart disease.','<p>Current360 strategy included reaching consumers who want the best for their pets and seek out reliable information from trusted sources. A blogger outreach program was developed to reach those influential in the pet space and begin educating them and their followers.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>To support this initiative, OraStrip also launched an Instagram account at BlogPaws, a national pet blogger conference. A contest was created using the account that encouraged bloggers to Instagram a picture of their dog and tag it #MyDogsSmile.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Participants were able to pick up a #MyDogsSmile bandana at the OraStrip booth, where a QuickCheck test would be performed on their pet. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>After the conference, the account continued to evolve for a period of time. The profile, titled “My Dog’s Smile” (brought to you by OraStrip), featured a feed of the best dog photos tagged #MyDogsSmile.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Photos, as well OraStrip’s own photos, were frequently shared along with the dogs facts, contest opportunities, OraStrip Twitter chat announcements and soft messages about the importance of healthy pet oral hygiene.</p>','The Instagram account has helped to launch a dialogue about pet oral health among more than a dozen influential bloggers, create product awareness and encourage veterinary visits. It has also helped OraStrip amplify its brand presence online.\r\n','Placeholder OraStrip Quote','A. Person',6,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-21 17:52:17','2015-05-22 15:43:23','orastrip'),(21,'Louisville Ladder','Assist Louisville Ladder in launching DeWalt and Black & Decker branded ladders in the construction and consumer markets.','While Louisville Ladder is a leading brand in the professional construction market, Werner owns the consumer market for ladder sales in the United States. In order for Louisville Ladder to compete and gain share, they needed to reach more customers and offer products that would resonate with the construction and consumer audiences. In short, they needed to find a way into Lowe’s.\r\n','<p>Louisville Ladder made a significant investment to license the DeWalt and Black & Decker brands in order to add recognizable, well-established names to the ladder category.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Then they came to Current360 for help getting into test markets with one of the largest home improvement retail chains in North America. Current360 could offer significant retail experience with several clients – including Mattress & More and Furniture Liquidators – and we had successfully placed products into large retail stores, like Walmart and Costco. But we didn’t know much about ladders.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>So we had to get up to speed. Quickly. Beyond basic product research, we spoke with experts and conducted surveys. We even interviewed consumers in Lowe’s parking lots to gain valuable insight into their brand loyalty.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Then we had to fully digest and embrace DeWalt and Black & Decker brand standards, as well as Lowe’s packaging, merchandising and marketing restrictions, in order to produce all the necessary presentation materials.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Within one month, we developed comprehensive planograms, packaging, sales materials, POS examples, leave behinds, motion graphic videos and interview videos for the Lowe’s pitch. The Current360 team members even presented side-by-side with Louisville Ladder’s sales team to help convince Lowe’s that DeWalt and Black & Decker ladder brands would be in demand.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Beyond the presentation to Lowe’s, we also designed Louisville Ladder’s booth at the National Hardware Tradeshow to formally launch the new products.</p>','The Louisville Ladder team’s presentation was successful, and Lowe’s accepted the products into test markets in Texas and Arizona.','Placeholder Louisville Ladder Quote','A. Person',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-21 17:53:55','2015-05-22 15:43:23','louisville-ladder'),(22,'Mattress & More','To remain competitive in a saturated market of high-volume mattress retailers during a recession, Mattress & More needed an innovative strategy to reach consumers.','During periods of economic uncertainty, household budgets tighten up and large purchases are made less frequently. Potential mattress customers are more likely to simply make do with their current beds until signs of recovery. Those who decide to move forward with a mattress purchase in spite of this trend often conduct a significant amount of online research first. They see the recession as an opportunity to find the best possible value. These consumers tend to read reviews, then compare prices from different retailers in order to make a purchase decision well before entering the actual store.','<p>Due to this increase in comparison-shopping, Current360 knew that captivated online consumers would be looking for a bigger, better deal. We partnered with Mattress & More to plan and execute annual promotional calendars with more than 20 promotional windows. These were comprised of varying sale events and multiple forms of media messaging to cut through the clutter and speak directly to value-seeking consumers. Additionally, we carefully monitored ad spending to ensure adequate coverage for each store’s marketing needs.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Current360 also executed media buys under the turn-on-a-dime demands of high-impact retail throughout the campaign. Since Mattress & More offers multiple mattress brands – including Sealy® and Tempur-Pedic® – we contracted and stewarded all broadcast and digital media for each brand. Then, we coordinated with national brand vendors to orchestrate each promotion through traditional and digital media.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Data showed that the majority of our target audience conducted their product research on Bing and Google. So Current360 implemented a disruptive search pay-per-click campaign consisting of keywords relevant to the queries those consumers are already using.</p>','<p>The online campaign proved to be a success, as sales remained steady despite the difficult economic conditions. By utilizing the most current text ad optimizations – like ad extensions – Mattress & More ads occupied greater real estate and higher ad rank than their competition, which provided better click-through rates at a lower cost-per-click.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Since partnering with Mattress & More in 2006, Current360 has successfully guided them through the opening of seven new stores and three new markets. This has translated into a 35% increase in corporate growth.</p>','Placeholder Mattress and More quote','A. Person',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-21 17:55:25','2015-05-22 15:43:23','mattress-more'),(23,'Clark Memorial Hospital','Clark Memorial Hospital wanted to convey that residents of southern Indiana could expect high-quality healthcare from a hospital that truly cares about their needs, along with the needs of their family members, their neighbors and their overall community.','Incorporating sincerity, authenticity and honesty makes it possible to appeal to multiple generations and build a strong, personal relationship between the hospital and the people they want to reach.','<p>To create a human connection, we took a closer look into the motivations of former patients and current providers. We wanted to know – with all the healthcare options available in the area – why they chose Clark. So we conducted interviews, hoping to uncover a few heart-warming stories that we could build a campaign around.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Fortunately, Clark Memorial already has a strong reputation for exceptional healthcare. We were told story after story of staff members going above the call of duty, parents returning for the births of their second and third children and physicians taking pride in offering the latest treatment options so that their patients wouldn’t be forced to leave the community.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>The consistency in which we heard about these positive experiences made us comfortable that the concept reflected the true personality of the hospital. We also knew that we would have more than enough material to continue the campaign for years. For our marketing executions, we simply retold these stories and featured the actual patients and physicians in their own environments.</p>','Our strategy was proven effective as our message resonated among residents of southern Indiana.  Hospital services lines featured in the campaign realized increases in both office visits — up to 43% — and Relative Value Units (RVUs) — up to 83%.  Consumers are now identifying Clark Memorial as their community’s hospital of choice. Of course, they also enjoy recognizing their friends and neighbors from the various campaign materials.\r\n','Placeholder Clark Memorial Quote','A. Person',0,'main.jpg',NULL,NULL,'ClarkMemorialHospital.jpg',NULL,'2015-05-21 17:56:43','2015-05-27 22:06:59','clark-memorial-hospital'),(24,'Belle Centennial Festival','Encourage visitors to participate in historic riverboat cruises during the Belle of Louisville’s 100th birthday celebration.','The success of any event is determined by ticket sales and overall attendance. And, as a one-time festival, it would be vital to secure sponsors and raise funds as early as possible in order to attract a large number of attendees. We also recognized the need to speak to a wide range of potential audiences, from history buffs and riverboat enthusiasts to local residents looking for a fun, family event along the Ohio River.\r\n','<p>Current360 began working on the Centennial Festival of Riverboats (the name for the six-day event) and Belle’s Big Birthday Bash (the Belle of Louisville’s 100th birthday celebration on Saturday) more than two years before the event took place.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We needed to position the Festival as a once-in-a-lifetime event in riverboat history, and a celebration worthy of the oldest operating Mississippi River-style steamboat in the world. Most important, we needed to create demand for over 100 public riverboat cruises – from dinner and Bourbon-tasting cruises to races, parades and historical tours – that required ticket purchases.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>While the Festival team worked to bring in riverboats from around the country and plan activities on both Louisville and Indiana waterfronts, the Current360 team began working on marketing materials. Logos, type treatments, collateral pieces – including rack cards, brochures and sales materials – and a website were created. We also developed a video and television spot featuring Governor Steve Beshear, Louisville Mayor Greg Fischer and David Karem, President of the Waterfront Development Corporation. These pieces helped to secure sponsors and armed tourism organizations throughout the region with useful materials.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We also recognized that this event offered many fun events and opportunities beyond the historic riverboats. By promoting everything that the Centennial Festival of Riverboats would offer – including food, Bourbon, music and art – along with all the attractions around Louisville, we were able to add significant value to the experience and convince more people to visit.</p>','Through the collaborative efforts of Current360 and the Waterfront Development Corporation, more than 18,000 tickets were sold – representing visitors from 45 states and eight different countries – and an estimated 100,000 people visited the event.\r\n','Placeholder Belle quote','A. Person',10,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-21 17:58:29','2015-05-22 15:43:23','belle-centennial-festival'),(25,'Texas Steakhouse','In 2008, Current360 was retained by the casual dining concept Texas Steakhouse and Saloon to assist in reversing a three-year trend of declining guest counts and attractively position the 20+-unit chain to be sold.','Texas Steakhouse operated multiple units in North Carolina, Virginia and West Virginia. During this time, the entire country was experiencing an economic downturn. And the casual dining segment was getting hit especially hard. Texas Steakhouse found itself losing customers faster than they could be replaced.\r\n','To combat these trends, Current360 recognized the primary importance of retaining existing customers above the more costly approach of relying upon the acquisition of new customers alone. Texas needed to encourage loyalty and transform customers into positive-promoters of the brand. This led to the launch of \"Real Texan Rewards\" program, an online program loaded with tangible benefits. Beginning in August of 2009, customers who provided varying levels of information or actions were eligible to become Bronze, Silver or Gold \"Spurs.\" Rewards varied from exclusive offers and call-ahead seating to a photo ID card, priority seating and branded apparel. \r\n \r\nWhat was unique in our approach versus a typical restaurant loyalty program was the strategy of rewarding the customer with an enhanced brand experience or branded premiums that doubled as awareness generators — instead of simply giving away free food based upon a tiered “points” system. The program was specifically designed to build brand equity without discounting the brand, while also making current customers enthusiastic, authentic ambassadors for Texas Steakhouse. ','<p>In 2008, Texas Steakhouse was experiencing negative customer counts of nearly 5%.  By 2011, after 18 months of the Real Texan Rewards program, customer counts were up a healthy 3.8% and trending higher. Over those three years, we enrolled more than 120,000 customers in the Real Texan Rewards program. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>This turnaround also helped Texas Steakhouse and Saloon accomplish their second goal, as the restaurant concept was successfully sold in 2012.</p>\r\n','Placeholder Texas Quote','A. Person',2,'main.jpg',NULL,NULL,'TexasLogo.jpg',NULL,'2015-05-21 18:01:32','2015-05-22 15:43:23','texas-steakhouse'),(26,'Tumbleweed','Tumbleweed Tex Mex Grill & Margarita Bar needed to establish a niche within the casual dining category.','<p>Even though the cuisine had been around since the 1800s, consumers struggled to understand what defined Tex Mex cooking. Initial research revealed that most people identified it as either BBQ or Mexican food, with some having no idea what Tex Mex meant at all. Beyond that, most were completely unaware of what made Tex Mex authentic, like cooking foods over real Mesquite logs or using fresh ingredients from the American Southwest.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Another obstacle was brand consistency. As Tumbleweed grew across the region, the restaurant had come to mean different things to different people. In some cities, it was a considered a steakhouse. In other areas, it was the place to go for spicy foods and ice-cold margaritas. To become synonymous with true Tex Mex cuisine, every customer’s expectations and experiences would need to be the same for each restaurant location.</p>\r\n','<p>First things first, we set out to educate the general public about Tex Mex cooking. Bookended 15-second television spots and full-page print ads featured a combination of colorful graphics and photography to grab our audiences’ attention. Each highlighted an individual ingredient – including avocados, peppers and agave plants – or traditional favorites – like ribs, burritos and margaritas.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>This approach reminded key demographics that they already love many core Tex Mex items, while at the same time positioning Tumbleweed as a completely different dining option. Limited time offers helped to drive trials and return visits, and a new tagline of “This is Tex Mex. This is Tumbleweed.” reinforced our overall brand identity. The Tumbleweed website was also redesigned to incorporate the new look and feel.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Next, we addressed Tumbleweed’s overall look. Fresh Tex Mex ingredients are naturally bright and colorful, so we redesigned everything — from interior decor to new menus — to match that appeal. This helped to reflect our overall attitude as a fun, festive place where customers can escape from their daily lives.</p>','We’re continuing to see success as the campaign grows and evolves. In its primary markets, more than 70% identify Tumbleweed Tex Mex Grill & Margarita Bar as the most closely associated with Tex Mex during unaided recall awareness tests. Even in areas saturated with Mexican restaurants and steakhouses, Tumbleweed is stealing share as consumers are now seeking out authentic Tex Mex cuisine. ','Placeholder Tumbleweed Quote','A. Person',2,'main.jpg',NULL,NULL,'TumbleweedLogo.jpg',NULL,'2015-05-21 18:03:30','2015-05-22 15:43:23','tumbleweed'),(27,'RELAX Wines','RELAX® Wines needed to secure a relationship with their fan base and reward their best fans.\r\n','Millennials are loyal to the brands that connect with them on a personal level. As a result, they become valuable influencers, especially through social media. Of course, the social landscape is constantly evolving. While Facebook may be the most popular destination for RELAX fans right now, we had to think about what would happen if/when that or any social network dissolves for the next big thing. It became clear that – in a worst-case scenario – our current relationships could dissolve as well.\r\n','<p>We decided to eliminate the intermediary by bringing RELAX’s best customers directly to us and establishing a brand ambassador group. So Current360 built a custom fan engagement platform that combines email, web and all the major social networks with engaging elements of gamification.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>By creating something original, relevant and hassle-free, we spoke to the values of RELAX’s core Millennial audience. And we aligned with their existing digital habits.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Our exclusive group of RELAX fanatics (who we call Sipsters) now have the ability to connect with each other and share their love of our wines. Through various interactions – like social media mentions, new member recruitment and Instagram challenges – Sipsters are recognized with points and badges. They then earn RELAX branded gifts as rewards for reaching point milestones, which encourages them to continue sharing authentic experiences with friends.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Several times per week, exclusive content is posted for Sipsters on our RELAXNation blog. For content inspiration, our social media team looks to lifestyle topics trending within the audience. We then craft recipes, DIY projects, event how-tos and other content that align with the RELAX lifestyle. Sipsters also frequently receive handwritten “thank you” notes, free downloads and random giveaway items that help to activate brand advocates, reward loyalty and encourage word-of-mouth sharing.</p>\r\n','In the first quarter following the launch of Sipsters, RELAX Wines experienced a significant online brand lift with a 577% increase in online public mentions compared to the previous quarter. Our efforts also reached nearly 200,000 additional people on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram in the 1st quarter. Careful content curation and gaming mechanisms have also resulted in an active community that resonates with RELAX consumers, which has led to an increase in brand loyalty, online reach and – most important – product sales.\r\n','Placeholder Relax Quote','A. Person',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-21 18:04:57','2015-05-22 15:43:23','relax-wines'),(28,'The Greater Louisville YMCA','After a record-breaking year for enrollment in 2013, we were challenged by The Greater Louisville YMCA to boost new membership acquisitions and existing member renewals even further the following year.','While achieving marketing objectives and membership goals is a yearlong process, it’s no secret that the four-week membership drive following Christmas is the most critical time. This is when New Year’s resolutions are in full swing, and the majority of gyms in the Louisville market are promoting their lowest prices and their newest equipment.','<p>The Y is already synonymous with healthy living. We needed to reinforce their position of being much more than a typical “gym and swim” to maximize memberships. That required increased awareness of the Y’s social responsibility efforts and youth development initiatives to the key audiences of singles, families and senior citizens. To be successful, we had to convince potential members that the Y’s overall community and wellness benefits provided an exceptional value for the monthly price.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>We developed a comprehensive campaign around the theme, “Be healthy. Be strong. Belong.” This message clearly conveyed that Y is a place where everyone can come together to improve their physical fitness and contribute to a better community. We brought the line to life by producing a television spot using actual members to illustrate how the Y benefits everyone in the family. Then, we carried our message through print, outdoor and direct mail executions to increase awareness and push promotional membership opportunities.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>During the peak membership months of January, May and June, we reinforced our traditional media tactics with digital ­search text and display image ads along with paid Facebook posts. We also created a guerilla marketing campaign. Members of the downtown Y staff dressed as – wait for it – gorillas and interrupted high foot-traffic areas with bananas and a message to visit the Y during lunch for a free snack. This helped us break through the clutter and promote downtown memberships directly to our surrounding target audiences.</p>','These tactics – in tandem with the exceptional efforts of the Y’s own staff – helped to increase new and renewing household memberships beyond the previous record-breaking year. Specifically, our digital campaign produced results that exceeded our campaign goals, with click-though rates more than 3 times our initial goal and an average cost per click at nearly half of our intended target. \r\n','As someone who practically grew up at the Y, it is especially fulfilling for me to be a partner in their success.','Harry Mulkey',9,'main.jpg',NULL,NULL,'YMCA-logo.jpg',NULL,'2015-05-21 19:46:59','2015-05-22 15:43:23','the-greater-louisville-ymca');
